Interface DirectedGraph<E>

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AdjacencyListGraph

    public interface DirectedGraph<E>
    Provides the interface for a graph implementation that provides functionality that includes the addition/deletion of nodes and the edges associated with those nodes. This interface also provides functionality that includes whether an object appears in the graph, if two objects have an edge between them, and providing the number of vertices/edges in the graph.
    Author:
    Hayden Charles Smith, z3418003
    Last modified: 19th May 2013
